<plot>The short brings to life pages from Fawcett Publications' "Mechanix Illustrated" magazine showing segments of making illuminating gas (neon) from coke; the assembly of a light airplane designed for the civilian pilot; clay-fashioning, and subsequent casting, of figures used in department store window-displays; and the making of cosmetics.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?642080</url></doc>
